<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1439,266,1084]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
Large sized, dark reddish flies, 
<quantity box="[528,615,298,324]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.9" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" unit="mm" value="29.0">29 mm</quantity>
. The species has a very “shaggy” appearance with long trailing hair. The abdomen is for the most part shiny black. It is the largest of the South Korean 
<taxonomicName box="[1147,1241,338,363]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Laphria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1147,1241,338,363]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Laphria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
recorded in this study.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1439,266,1084]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,659,418,444]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Redescription based on single male.</emphasis>
Head: Face black integument, gold pollen and gold hair. Long, dense mystax yellow/gold/red. Parafacial hair long, gold. Short, sparse gold and black orbital hair. Proboscis apex angulated (similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[464,627,498,523]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Choerades" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caucasicus">
<emphasis box="[464,627,498,523]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">C. caucasicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<figureCitation box="[641,728,498,524]" captionStart="FIGURES 24 – 28" captionStartId="10.[151,269,1976,2000]" captionTargetBox="[425,1189,474,1975]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[397,1189,474,1986]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 24 – 28. Heads. 24. C. amurensis. 25. Orthogonis sp. 26. C. sp. 27. C. caudatus. 28. C. caucasicus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/175158/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
Fig. 
<number box="[695,728,498,524]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="28.0">28</number>
</figureCitation>
). Short black and gold postocular hair. Ocellar tubercle with 
<number box="[151,166,538,564]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="3.0">3</number>
short, yellow bristles. Antenna black with gold hair; relative lengths of segments: 
<number box="[1143,1158,538,564]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="3.0">3</number>
&gt; 
<number box="[1177,1188,538,564]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1.0">1</number>
&gt; 
<number box="[1206,1223,538,564]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="2.0">2</number>
; postpedicel (segment 
<number box="[218,233,578,604]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="3.0">3</number>
) with apical pit. Thorax: Dorsal scutum black integument; lateral surfaces with bright red hair. Postpronotal hair red. Chaetotaxy with notopleural, supraalar and postalar surfaces covered in dense long, bright red bristles and hair. Sparse, fine dark red dorsocentral hair erect above appressed lighter red hair. Scutellar margin widely lipped, ringed with long red bristles. Lateral aspect of thorax black, light gold pollinose and long, dense, red hair. Anterior anepisternum with short red hair; posterior with dense long red hair and 
<number box="[1422,1437,738,764]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="2.0">2</number>
strong black bristles. Katatergal bristles abundant, mostly red, some black. Legs: Entirely black with dense white, yellow and red hair. 
<collectingCountry box="[474,533,818,844]" name="India" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Hind</collectingCountry>
femur swollen apically. Wings: Tinged brown surrounding veins. Abdomen: Tergites black with yellow hair. Tergites 
<number box="[625,669,858,884]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="2.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="1.0">1–4</number>
with sparse, erect yellow hair; apical tergites with hair appressed. Lateral areas of tergites with long sparse yellow and black hair. Male genitalia as in 
<figureCitation box="[1232,1325,898,924]" captionStart="FIGURES 29 – 32" captionStartId="11.[151,269,1613,1637]" captionTargetBox="[303,1283,565,1612]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[303,1284,565,1626]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 29 – 32. Laphria — male genitalia. 29. L. hakiensis, lateral. 30. L. mitsukurri, lateral. 31. L. mitsukurri, gonopod. 32. L. rufa, gonopod." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/175159/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
Fig. 
<number box="[1292,1325,898,924]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="29.0">29</number>
</figureCitation>
. Female: Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
